text: The Namdapha flying frog, Namdapha tree frog, Namdapha bush frog, red-webbed tree frog, red-webbed flying frog, red-webbed whipping tree frog, orange- webbed tree frog, or twin-spotted tree frog (Rhacophorus rhodopus) is a frog. It lives in Myanmar, China, India, and Laos. People have seen it between 1200 and 2200 meters above sea level. ==First paper== * ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Rhacophorus rhodopus
